Welcome back to Dry Powder. I=E2=80=99m Bill Cohan.

In today=E2=80=99s
issue, a close look at another Bill Ackman micro-scandal that erupted acros=
s my X feed in recent days, wherein the prolix hedge fund manager found him=
self vigorously defending a podcast appearance in which he seemed to take s=
everal potshots at his hero and =E2=80=9Cunofficial mentor,=E2=80=9D Warren=
 Buffett. Ackman, of course, is in the midst of attempting to stand up his =
own version of Berkshire Hathaway, which made the alleged attacks appear al=
l the more pointed. The
interview itself offered some news, which I share below alongside some obse=
rvations on the incident writ large. Also in this email: my analysis of how=
 Elon=E2=80=99s West Wing side gig is hurting Tesla shareholders, and some =
important news from my partner Eriq Gardner on the latest wrinkle in the Pa=
ramount-Skydance deal.

